        "*   The `servicos` table was successfully refactored and renamed to `ordens_servico`, incorporating new columns: `pecas_sugeridas_mecanico` (for mechanic's suggestions with multiple brands), `pecas_aprovadas_admin` (for admin's approved parts with a final brand), and `valor_comissao_mecanico` (to store the calculated commission value).\n",
        "*   All core functions (`registar_colaborador`, `registar_servico`, `sugerir_pecas_mecanico`, `aprovar_rejeitar_pecas_admin`, `get_servicos_mecanico`, `get_solicitacoes_pecas_pendentes`) were updated to correctly interact with the new `ordens_servico` table, ensuring data consistency and integrity across the system.\n",
        "*   The `aprovar_rejeitar_pecas_admin` function now supports detailed part approval, allowing administrators to select a specific brand for each approved part, define the total service value (e.g., R\\$850.00), and set the mechanic's commission percentage (e.g., 15.0%).\n",
        "*   The system accurately calculates the `valor_comissao_mecanico` based on the total service value and the commission percentage (e.g., for a R\\$850.00 service with a 15% commission, the value calculated was R\\$127.50).\n",
        "*   The viewing functions (`get_servicos_mecanico` and `get_solicitacoes_pecas_pendentes`) were enhanced to correctly retrieve and display all new details, including suggested and approved part brands, service total, commission percentage, and the calculated commission value, presenting a comprehensive overview to both mechanics and administrators.\n",
